# multi-tenant/v1 — RESERVED v2.2 example: quota exceeded
#
# This exchange illustrates the 429 + Retry-After response envelope that
# agentic-sandbox v2.2 emits when a tenant exceeds its configured dispatch
# rate. It is RESERVED — agentic-sandbox v2.0 (declared tier) MUST NOT emit
# this response from its quota machinery, and v2.0 conformance harnesses
# MUST NOT assert it.
#
# Scenario: tenant 'aiwg-prod' has a per-tenant dispatch rate limit of
# 100 requests per 60 seconds. The 101st request inside the window is
# rejected with HTTP 429. The client is instructed to retry after 12 s.
#
# Wire shape: spec.md §4.3; quota-response.schema.json.
# Tier: stable (v2.2 only).

### Request — the dispatch that trips the rate limit

POST /a2a HTTP/1.1
Host: sandbox.example.net
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOi...REDACTED...
A2A-Extensions: https://agentic-sandbox.aiwg.io/extensions/multi-tenant/v1
Content-Length: 412

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": "req-7f3a-101",
  "method": "message/send",
  "params": {
    "message": {
      "kind": "message",
      "messageId": "01HM4ZB2D7K8X9V3Q4P1S5T6R7",
      "role": "user",
      "parts": [
        { "kind": "text", "text": "Dispatch number 101 in the window." }
      ],
      "metadata": { "tenant_id": "aiwg-prod" }
    }
  }
}

### Response — 429 Too Many Requests

HTTP/1.1 429 Too Many Requests
Content-Type: application/json
Retry-After: 12
A2A-Extensions: https://agentic-sandbox.aiwg.io/extensions/multi-tenant/v1
Content-Length: 296

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": "req-7f3a-101",
  "error": {
    "code": -32029,
    "message": "Tenant quota exceeded",
    "data": {
      "tenant_id": "aiwg-prod",
      "quota": "rate",
      "retry_after_seconds": 12,
      "limit": 100,
      "window_seconds": 60
    }
  }
}

### Notes
#
# - HTTP status MUST be 429 (RFC 6585).
# - Retry-After header MUST be present, integer delta-seconds form
#   (RFC 7231 §7.1.3), and MUST equal error.data.retry_after_seconds.
# - error.code MUST be -32029 (sandbox-reserved JSON-RPC application code
#   for tenant quota exhaustion).
# - error.data.tenant_id MUST equal the request's Message.metadata.tenant_id
#   (or 'default' if the request omitted it).
# - error.data.quota is one of "rate" | "concurrency". For concurrency-cap
#   exhaustion the same envelope is used with quota = "concurrency" and
#   window_seconds omitted.
# - error.data.limit and error.data.window_seconds MAY be redacted by
#   operators who consider configured quotas sensitive (spec.md §8.5).
# - tenant_id 'aiwg-prod' would have been bound to the bearer token by the
#   auth layer; the quota response is not the place to authenticate.
#   See spec.md §8.2.
